Quote:  A long sentence may be called <i>the big Huey (Long)</i>, in reference to Governor Huey Long of Louisiana, notorious for his harsh sentences, and a life sentence may be referred to as <i>doing the lot, all up</i>, or the <i>bitch</i>.
